sql:
SELECT ie_name, assigned_criticality
FROM information_elements
WHERE presence = 'Mandatory';

external_knowledge:
- 'treasure chest of highly critical information' refers to high-criticality information elements (IEs) with a criticality level of 'High';
- 'frequently' means more than once within the last 30 days;
- '5G NR protocol creators' are users associated with the '5G NR' protocol.

'5G NR' protocol refers to the 5th generation New Radio protocol; protocol_id 0 is used to identify this protocol in the database; 
Information Elements (IEs) are the basic building blocks of data exchange in the 5G network; 
Criticality levels (High, Medium, Low) indicate the importance of each IE to the network's functioning.
